The paper deals with online detection of changes in data sequences, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. The use of Bayesian methods and online algorithms suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus on temporal scaling and medical data sets suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.ST (Statistics). The use of prediction and inference also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the use of probabilistic models and inference algorithms suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
